data.name: Tofu Buddha Bowl
data.quickTastyDescription: A vibrant and nutritious bowl filled with seasoned tofu, fresh vegetables, and a delicious dressing.
detailedCookingInstructions: Press the tofu for about 10 minutes to remove excess moisture.
Cut the pressed tofu into cubes and marinate in soy sauce and olive oil for 10 minutes.
Heat a skillet over medium heat and cook the marinated tofu for about 10 minutes, turning occasionally until golden brown.
In a bowl, add cooked quinoa as the base.
Top with spinach, shredded carrot, sliced cucumber, and avocado.
Add the cooked tofu on top of the vegetables.
Drizzle lime juice and sprinkle sesame seeds over the bowl.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
data.detailedName: Tofu Buddha Bowl with Quinoa and Fresh Vegetables
